{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Albrecht Penck Glacier | other_name = | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Albrecht Penck Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Victoria Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|76|40|S|162|20|E|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Tripp Bay]] | status = | embedded = }}
'''Albrecht Penck Glacier''' ({{coord|76|40|S|162|20|E|type:glacier_region:AQ|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]] between the [[Fry Glacier]] and the [[Evans Piedmont Glacier]], draining northeast toward [[Tripp Bay]] on the coast of [[Victoria Land]], [[Antarctica]]. It was first charted by the [[Nimrod Expedition|British Antarctic Expedition]] (1907&ndash;09) which named this feature for [[Albrecht Penck]], the Director of the Institute of Oceanography and of the Geographical Institute in [[Berlin]].<ref>{{usgs-gazetteer|id=204}}</ref>
