{{Infobox Mars crater
| name        = Babakin (crater)
| image       = [[File:BabakinMartianCrater.jpg|350px]]
| caption     = MOLA map of Babakin crater
| coordinates = {{coord|36|S|71.44|W|globe:mars_type:landmark|display=inline,title}}
| region = [[Thaumasia quadrangle]]
| discoverer  = 
| diameter    = 76.66 km
| eponym      = [[Georgy Babakin|Babakin]]
}}
'''Babakin''' is a crater in the northeast of [[Thaumasia quadrangle]] of Mars, located in the northeast of [[Aonia Terra]] located southwest of [[Bosporos Planum]] and further southeast of Coracis Fossae. The crater is  located at 36°S latitude and 71.44°W longitude.  It is 76.66&nbsp;km in diameter and was named after [[Georgy Babakin|Babakin]]. Its name was approved in 1985.<ref>{{cite web|work=Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature (USGS)|title=Babakin|url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/532|publisher=[[International Astronomical Union]]|accessdate=June 13, 2018}}</ref>

East is the tiny crater Kumak and further west are Pulawy and the much smaller Los, both located at Coracis Fossae.

In the mid-northeast portion inside the crater is a smaller crater named '''Gari''', it is named for a [[Gari, Russia|town in Russia]].

