'''Balch''' is a [[list of craters on Venus|crater on Venus]] at latitude 29.9, longitude 282.9 in Devana Chasma, Central Beta Regio. It is 40&nbsp;km in diameter and named after [[Emily Balch]], though it was originally designated Somerville crater. This crater is one of the few examples of tectonically modified craters seen on Venus. The absence of such craters indicates a possible cessation of tectonic deformation on Venus at some point in history.

