{{about||the Danish pianist and organist|Christian Christiansen (musician)|the Danish filmmaker|Christian E. Christiansen}} {{Infobox person | name = Christian Christiansen | image = File:Nap ChristiansenChristian01.jpg | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1843|10|09}} | birth_place = | death_date = {{Death date and age|1917|11|28|1843|10|09}} | death_place = | nationality = Danish | other_names = | occupation = | years_active = 1870s-1912 | known_for = [[Christiansen effect]] | notable_works = }}
'''Christian Christiansen''' (9 October 1843 in [[Lønborg]], [[Denmark]] – 28 November 1917 [[Frederiksberg]]) was a Danish physicist.
Christiansen first taught at the local polytechnical school. In 1886, he was appointed to a chair for physics at the [[University of Copenhagen]].
He mainly studied [[radiant heat]] and [[dispersion (optics)|optical dispersion]], discovering the [[Christiansen effect]] (Christiansen filter). Around 1917, he discovered the [[anomalous dispersion]] of numerous dyes, including [[Fuchsine|aniline red]] (fuchsine), by recording [[absorption spectrum|absorption spectra]].
In 1884, he confirmed the [[Stefan–Boltzmann law]].
Christiansen was elected a member of the [[Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences]] in 1902.
He was doctoral advisor to [[Niels Bohr]]. In 1912, he retired and [[Martin Knudsen]] became professor.
==Citations== * C. Christiansen, ''Lærebog i fysik'', Copenhagen, 1892 * C. Christiansen, ''Indledning til den mathematiske Fysik'', 2 Bde, 1887-1889 * C. Christiansen, ''Untersuchungen über die optischen Eigenschaften von fein vertheilten Körpern - Erste Mittheilung'', [http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k15266v.pagination Ann. Phys., Vol. 23], pp.&nbsp;298–306, 1884 * C. Christiansen, ''Untersuchungen über die optischen Eigenschaften von fein vertheilten Körpern - Zweite Mittheilung'', [http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k152676.pagination Ann. Phys., vol. 24], pp.&nbsp;439–446, 1885 * C. Christiansen ''[https://archive.org/details/elementsoftheore00chriiala Elements of Theoretical Physics]'' translated into English by [[William Francis Magie|W. F. Magie]] from the German translation of Johannes Julius Christoph Müller (London, McMillan, 1897)<ref>{{cite journal|author=Mackenzie, A. Stanley|authorlink=Arthur Stanley Mackenzie|title=Review: ''Elements of Theoretical Physics'' by C. Christiansen, translated into English by W. F. Magie|journal=Bull. Amer. Math. Soc.|year=1898|volume=4|issue=6|pages=276–277|url=http://www.ams.org/journals/bull/1898-04-06/S0002-9904-1898-00496-2/S0002-9904-1898-00496-2.pdf|doi=10.1090/s0002-9904-1898-00496-2}}</ref>
